		<a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8714'>Xanthix</a></font> <font class="afont">( was very helpful )</font></TD></TR><TR><TD align='right' valign='top'><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top'><font class="bfont">This article treads that fine line between being card oriented and dealing with the bigger picture, so it&#39;s hard to know how high my scale should go.  For that reason, I&#39;m giving you 4.5 stars and rounding up.<br>
<br>
First of all, some things to work on in the future.  Perhaps it was just me, but I felt like this article had some transition problems.  The flow was a little disjointed and choppy.  Not much, mind you, but enough to force me to read certain sections again because I didn&#39;t get the whole idea the first time.  I think part of the reason your article had this feel is that you started us off with some objectives for beating the swarm and never really discussed why these would work.  You went straight into examples.  Now, the examples were good and very worth the read, but some of the more tentative Decktechers might not simply take your suggestions on faith.  Perhaps it would have also behooved you to begin your intro with a more situational example.  Orcs returning because of Goblin Swarms and They Are Coming and you looking at 12 orcs with a 5 companion fellowship.  You get the picture.  This also leads me into my other major criticism.  Your conclusion was extremely weak.  Now, I know I have written some weak conlusions myself, but the key is that the conclusion should tell your audience what you want them to remember by reemphasizing key points and adding a little bit of entertaining punch as well.  You did the punch, but not the emphasis.  Work on your conclusion in the future.<br>
<br>
Now, for the things that I really liked.  (Incidentally, you might think it strange that I have so much criticism for an article I give 5 stars, or even 4.5, but it&#39;s easier to critique good writing than it is horrible writing.)  Your points were very well supported.  Your suggestions were all sound.  Also, you documented the pros and cons of each strategy, which will help your audience to form their own opinions.  You layed out a number of possible solutions, so your audience has options.  And your format was very good for an article with many points.  You focused almost exclusively on Moria, but you did mention that Isengard and Sauron can swarm, which in turn provided a very thorough treatment of the swarms.  Overall, your content was excellent.  It just needs some work stylistically.  Keep up the good work, Glyph.  <font size=1>(+6 tp, Double-Edged Sword)</font><BR>
